Items.title: Angels home opener
Items.vs: Anaheim Angels vs. Texas Rangers

Items.description: Orlando Cabrera highlighted a four-run first inning with a two-run homer against Maddux and the Expos rolled to a 10-2 victory over the Atlanta Braves.
Items.title: Braves home opener
Items.vs: Atlanta Braves vs. Montreal Expos

Items.description: Brad Radke got 19 consecutive outs after a leadoff bunt single as Twins beat the Tigers 3-1 on Monday.
Items.title: Tigers home opener
Items.vs: Detroit Tigers vs. Minnesota Twins

Items.description: Chicago 15, New York 2
Items.title: Mets home opener
Items.vs: New York Mets vs. Chicago Cubs

Items.description: It was a strange opening day at Camden Yards -- even before a fly ball disappeared into a snowstorm.
Items.title: Orioles home opener
Items.vs: Baltimore Orioles vs. Cleveland Indians

Items.description: Runelvys Hernandez allowed two hits in six innings and rookie Angel Berroa drove in the go-ahead run as the Royals beat the Chicago White Sox 3-0 Monday
Items.title: Royals home opener
Items.vs: Kansas City Royals vs. Chicago White Sox

Items.description: Upgraded in a winter spending spree, the Philadelphia Phillies looked like much better ballclub on opening day. The team they beat looked like the same old Florida Marlins.
Items.title: Marlins home opener
Items.vs: Florida Marlins vs. Philadelphia Phillies

Items.description: They forgot to build a home-field advantage into the Cincinnati Reds' new ballpark.
Items.title: Reds home opener
Items.vs: Cincinnati Reds vs. Pittsburgh Pirates

Items.description: The St. Louis Cardinals are looking forward to a full season with Scott Rolen.
Items.title: Cardinals home opener
Items.vs: St. Louis Cardinals vs. Milwaukee Brewers

Items.description: Hideo Nomo pitched a four-hitter and the Los Angeles Dodgers handed Randy Johnson his first opening-day loss, beating the Arizona Diamondbacks 8-0 Monday.
Items.title: Diamondbacks home opener
Items.vs: Arizona Diamondbacks vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: Carl Crawford hit a three-run homer with two outs in the bottom of the ninth inning Monday, giving new manager Lou Piniella and the Tampa Bay Devil Rays a 6-4 victory over the Boston Red Sox.
Items.title: Devil Rays home opener
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Devil Rays vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Benito Santiago and J.T. Snow homered on consecutive pitches in the ninth inning, and the defending NL champion San Francisco Giants opened the season with a 5-2 win over the San Diego Padres on Monday.
Items.title: Padres home opener
Items.vs: San Diego Padres vs. San Francisco Giants

Items.description: A violent collision that left All-Star shortstop Derek Jeter with a dislocated left shoulder overshadowed all the good that happened for the New York Yankees on opening day.
Items.title: Blue Jays home opener
Items.vs: Toronto Blue Jays vs. New York Yankees

Items.description: The New York Yankees managed just fine without Derek Jeter, getting two homers from Jason Giambi and seven shutout innings from Andy Pettitte in a 10-1 victory over the Toronto Blue Jays on Tuesday.
Items.vs: Toronto Blue Jays vs. New York Yankees
Los Angeles Angels vs Texas Rangers

Items.description: After receiving their championship jewelry, the Anaheim Angels earned their first win of the year as Mickey Callaway tossed six strong innings in a 10-0 victory over the Texas Rangers.
Items.vs: Anaheim Angels vs. Texas Rangers
Oakland Athletics vs Seattle Mariners

Items.description: Erubiel Durazo doubled, homered and drove in all five runs and Tim Hudson allowed five hits in eight innings as the Athletics posted a 5-0 blanking of the Seattle Mariners in the season opener for both teams.
Items.title: Athletics home opener
Items.vs: Oakland Athletics vs. Seattle Mariners
San Diego Padres vs San Francisco Giants

Items.description: Jason Schmidt was almost unhittable before tiring in the eighth inning and Barry Bonds joined the San Francisco Giants' home run assault in an 8-1 rout of the San Diego Padres.
Items.vs: San Diego Padres vs. San Francisco Giants

Items.description: Jeff Kent hit a home run in his first at-bat for Houston and Jeff Bagwell homered twice as the Astros won their season opener Tuesday night, 10-4 over the Colorado Rockies.
Items.title: Astros home opener
Items.vs: Houston Astros vs. Colorado Rockies

Items.description: Kevin Millar homered with one out in the top of the 16th inning Tuesday night to give the Boston Red Sox a 9-8 victory over the Tampa Bay Devil Rays.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Devil Rays vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Junior Spivey's bases-loaded single in the 10th inning gave the Arizona Diamondbacks a 5-4 victory over the Los Angeles Dodgers on Tuesday night.
Items.vs: Arizona Diamondbacks vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: Joe Randa hit a tiebreaking two-run homer in the seventh inning as the Kansas City Royals beat the Chicago White Sox 5-4 Wednesday for their first 2-0 start in 24 years.
Items.vs: Kansas City Royals vs. Chicago White Sox
Oakland Athletics vs Seattle Mariners

Items.description: AL MVP Miguel Tejada hit a three-run homer and Cy Young winner Barry Zito pitched six solid innings as the Oakland Athletics beat the Seattle Mariners 8-3 Wednesday night.
Items.vs: Oakland Athletics vs. Seattle Mariners
San Diego Padres vs San Francisco Giants

Items.description: Marquis Grissom's three-run double highlighted a five-run third inning, and the San Francisco Giants beat the San Diego Padres 5-3 Wednesday night for a three-game sweep.
Items.vs: San Diego Padres vs. San Francisco Giants

Items.description: A historic home run by Alex Rodriguez wasn't enough for the Texas Rangers.
Items.vs: Anaheim Angels vs. Texas Rangers

Items.description: Zach Day and three relievers combined on a three-hitter, and Jose Vidro hit a two-run homer to lead the Montreal Expos over the Braves 3-0 Wednesday night.
Items.vs: Atlanta Braves vs. Montreal Expos

Items.description: The Cleveland Indians won their first game under new manager Eric Wedge, beating the Baltimore Orioles 4-2 Wednesday night behind a solid pitching performance by rookie Ricardo Rodriguez.
Items.vs: Baltimore Orioles vs. Cleveland Indians

Items.description: Jacque Jones hit a two-run homer and had four RBIs as the Minnesota Twins beat Detroit 8-1 Wednesday night in the major league debut of Jeremy Bonderman, the Tigers' 20-year-old right-hander.
Items.vs: Detroit Tigers vs. Minnesota Twins

Items.description: Randy Wolf took a one-hitter into the seventh inning, Jim Thome had two more hits and Mike Lieberthal added a bases-loaded triple to lead the Philadelphia Phillies over the Florida Marlins 8-2 Wednesday night.
Items.vs: Florida Marlins vs. Philadelphia Phillies

Items.description: New York 9, Toronto 7
Items.vs: Toronto Blue Jays vs. New York Yankees

Items.description: Kevin Young and Jason Kendall hit two-run homers in the eighth inning, and the Pittsburgh Pirates kept the Cincinnati Reds winless in their new ballpark by rallying for a 7-4 victory Wednesday night.
Items.vs: Cincinnati Reds vs. Pittsburgh Pirates

Items.description: Cliff Floyd hit a two-run homer deep into the right field bullpen in the first inning to lift the New York Mets to a 4-1 victory over the Chicago Cubs.
Items.vs: New York Mets vs. Chicago Cubs

Items.description: Jason Varitek hit a three-run homer and Derek Lowe shrugged off a shaky start to pitch six innings Wednesday night as the Boston Red Sox beat the Tampa Bay Devil Rays 7-5.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Devil Rays vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Craig Biggio's two-run single capped a rally from a four-run deficit in the ninth inning Wednesday night, giving the Houston Astros an 8-7 win over the Colorado Rockies.
Items.vs: Houston Astros vs. Colorado Rockies

Items.description: Woody Williams pitched two-hit ball into the seventh inning and Mike Matheny had three hits and two RBIs as the St. Louis Cardinals beat the Milwaukee Brewers 7-0 Wednesday night.
Items.vs: St. Louis Cardinals vs. Milwaukee Brewers

Items.description: Kevin Brown, in a performance that bodes well for the Los Angeles Dodgers, shut down the Arizona Diamondbacks on three hits in six-plus innings of a 5-0 victory Wednesday night.
Items.vs: Arizona Diamondbacks vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: The first guests at Great American Ball Park made off with everything but the towels.
Items.vs: Cincinnati Reds vs. Pittsburgh Pirates

Items.description: Kyle Lohse allowed two hits in eight innings as the Minnesota Twins beat the Detroit Tigers 3-0 Thursday to complete an opening three-game sweep.
Items.vs: Detroit Tigers vs. Minnesota Twins

Items.description: The Sammy Sosa traveling show packed up and left Shea Stadium on Thursday, still waiting for him to hit that elusive 500th home run.
Items.vs: New York Mets vs. Chicago Cubs

Items.description: Garrett Stephenson feels good, and it showed.
Items.vs: St. Louis Cardinals vs. Milwaukee Brewers

Items.description: Mark Redman gave the Florida Marlins a boost by throwing strikes, and they showed their appreciation by hitting home runs.
Items.vs: Florida Marlins vs. Philadelphia Phillies

Items.description: Nelson Cruz had something to prove to the Houston Astros.
Items.vs: Houston Astros vs. Colorado Rockies

Items.description: Brent Mayne hit a three-run homer in a seven-run eighth inning as the Kansas City Royals rallied to beat Chicago 12-6 Thursday for a three-game sweep of the White Sox.
Items.vs: Kansas City Royals vs. Chicago White Sox

Items.description: Kevin Millar homered and drove in four runs as the Boston Red Sox beat the Tampa Bay Devil Rays 14-5 Thursday.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Devil Rays vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Ben Davis hit a leadoff homer in the 11th inning as the Seattle Mariners blew two late leads but still got new manager Bob Melvin his first victory, beating the Oakland Athletics 7-6 Thursday.
Items.vs: Oakland Athletics vs. Seattle Mariners
